<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><lyrics>[V1]
 1. Thaumei dimsa'n, I gawzo dem,
 Moneipa hung tieng?
 I vakhawu le a thiengna dem?
 Moneipa hung tieng.
 Zie zan lopi tak a chun,
 I thaumei a vakna dem?
 Moneipa hung tieng.

[V2]
 Kiguong zo un! Kiguong zo un!
 Kiguong zo un! Moneipa hung tieng!

[V3]
 2. Lawpna aw gi I za ding um?
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Kipah aw gi I za ding um?
 Moneipa hung tieng.
 Zie zan lopi tak achun,
 I thaumei a vak na dem?
 Moneipa hung tieng.

[V4]
 3. I kiguotna vaigei lo di'n,
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Dan leh kikhenna umkhana,
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Zie zan lopi tak achun,
 I thaumei a vak na dem?
 Moneipa hung tieng.

[V5]
 4. Lungkhamna hun hithei ina,
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Thautui I hawlkhawm ding uchun,
 Moneipa hung tieng,
 Zie zan lopi tak a chun,
 I thaumei a vak na dem?
 Moneipa hung tieng.

[V6]
 5. Kikhawpna lopi um ina,
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Kimuokna lopi le um ding,
 Moneipa hung tieng;
 Zie zan kipahum zan chun,
 I thaumei vak hawihtak tawh,
 Moneipa hung tieng.</lyrics>
<title>WHEN THE BRIDEGROOM COMES</title>
<hymn_number>148</hymn_number>
</song>